# Persistence Rules (JPA — ADR-002)

## JPA Entity Rules
- JPA entities are **adapter concerns** — live in `adapter/out/persistence/entity/`
- Domain entities NEVER extend or reference JPA entities
- All JPA entities have `@Table(name = "...")` explicit table name
- Use `UUID` for primary keys, generated as `@UuidGenerator`
- Audit fields via `@EntityListeners(AuditingEntityListener.class)`

## DO ✅
```java
// JPA entity in adapter layer
@Entity
@Table(name = "orders")
public class OrderJpaEntity {

    @Id
    @UuidGenerator
    private UUID id;

    @Column(nullable = false)
    private String customerId;

    @Enumerated(EnumType.STRING)
    @Column(nullable = false)
    private OrderStatus status;

    @CreatedDate
    private Instant createdAt;

    @LastModifiedDate
    private Instant updatedAt;
}

// Repository interface — Spring Data only
public interface OrderJpaRepository extends JpaRepository<OrderJpaEntity, UUID> {
    List<OrderJpaEntity> findByCustomerIdAndStatus(String customerId, OrderStatus status);

    @Query("SELECT o FROM OrderJpaEntity o WHERE o.createdAt >= :from")
    Page<OrderJpaEntity> findRecentOrders(@Param("from") Instant from, Pageable pageable);
}
```

## DON'T ❌
```java
// Domain entity with JPA annotations
@Entity  // ❌ domain must not know JPA
public class Order {
    @Id
    private UUID id;
}

// Native SQL for simple queries
@Query(value = "SELECT * FROM orders WHERE customer_id = ?1", nativeQuery = true)  // ❌ use JPQL
```

## Mapping Pattern (MapStruct)
```java
@Mapper(componentModel = "spring")
public interface OrderPersistenceMapper {
    OrderJpaEntity toJpaEntity(Order domain);
    Order toDomain(OrderJpaEntity jpa);
    List<Order> toDomainList(List<OrderJpaEntity> jpaList);
}
```

## Repository Adapter Pattern
```java
// Implements domain port
@Component
@RequiredArgsConstructor
public class OrderRepositoryAdapter implements OrderRepository {

    private final OrderJpaRepository jpaRepository;
    private final OrderPersistenceMapper mapper;

    @Override
    public Order save(Order order) {
        return mapper.toDomain(jpaRepository.save(mapper.toJpaEntity(order)));
    }

    @Override
    public Optional<Order> findById(OrderId id) {
        return jpaRepository.findById(id.value()).map(mapper::toDomain);
    }
}
```

## Flyway Migration Rules
- File naming: `V{version}__{description}.sql` — e.g. `V001__create_orders_table.sql`
- Version is zero-padded 3 digits
- Each migration is **idempotent** where possible
- NEVER edit a committed migration — create a new one

## Checklist before PR
- [ ] JPA entity is in `adapter/out/persistence/entity/` package
- [ ] Domain entity has NO JPA imports
- [ ] MapStruct mapper exists for this entity
- [ ] Repository adapter implements domain port interface
- [ ] Flyway migration file created for schema changes
- [ ] Migration filename follows `V{3-digit}__{snake_description}.sql`
